{
  "texts": [
    "The identification of Hepatitis C-positive patients is performed using ICD-10 codes.",
    "We select the cohort of patients with Hepatitis C as their clinical notes are more likely to include information related to IDU.",
    "As explained in Section Note enrichment, we narrow down the clinical notes using a list of keywords/phrases indicative of IDU (refer to Table 2).",
    "To reduce computational overhead during training and because unusually large notes (determined by the outliers in the distribution of note lengths) may contain templated nonessential information that is not relevant to any specific patient, we remove some outlier notes based on the interquartile range of the note lengths.",
    "We later show in Section Error analysis that note length does not affect the performance of the model at the time of inference."
  ]
}